    "### 1. Market excess returns\n",
    "We download monthly data for the S\\&P 500 index (`^GSPC`) and the 13-week Treasury Bill rate (`^IRX`) from Yahoo! Finance for the period January 1, 2000 to February 28, 2026. The `^IRX` series is an annualized yield in percent, so it is converted into a monthly risk-free rate as\n",
    "$$\n",
    "r_{f,t} = (1 + IRX_t/100)^{1/12} - 1.\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Monthly excess market returns are then computed as\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\tilde r_{m,t} = r_{m,t} - r_{f,t},\n",
    "$$\n",
    "where $r_{m,t}$ denotes the monthly return on the S\\&P 500 index. We use the estimated monthly mean excess return $\\mu_m$ and monthly variance $\\sigma_m^2$ to calibrate the synthetic asset universe used in the remainder of the assignment.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "ex1-market-data",
