    "### 2. Synthetic asset universe\n",
    "Next, we construct a universe of $N = 50$ synthetic assets following the single-factor model:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\tilde r_{i,t} = \\beta_i \\tilde r_{m,t} + \\varepsilon_{i,t},\n",
    "$$\n",
    "where $\\varepsilon_{i,t}$ represents idiosyncratic risk. The factor loadings $\\beta_i$ and idiosyncratic volatilities $\\sigma_{\\varepsilon,i}$ are drawn from the distributions specified in the assignment. Using the estimated market moments from Exercise 1, we construct the true mean vector $\\mu$ and covariance matrix $\\Sigma$, which will be treated as the true parameters throughout the remainder of the assignment."
   ]
