    "\n",
    "### 5. Estimation error and the shape of the efficient frontier\n",
    "To study estimation error, we simulate asset returns from the true data-generating process and then replace the true moments by their sample counterparts $\\hat{\\mu}$ and $\\hat{\\Sigma}$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "ex5-simulate-returns",
   "metadata": {
    "cache": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| label: ex5-simulate-returns\n",
    "\n",
    "def simulate_returns(periods, expected_returns, covariance_matrix):\n",
    "    returns = np.random.multivariate_normal(\n",
    "        expected_returns,\n",
    "        covariance_matrix,\n",
    "        size=periods\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return returns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d477107e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We first compare the true frontier to the estimated frontier based on one simulated sample with $T=120$ monthly observations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "ex5-one-simulation",
   "metadata": {
    "cache": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| label: ex5-one-simulation\n",
    "#| echo: true\n",
    "\n",
    "T = 120\n",
    "\n",
    "simulated_returns = simulate_returns(T, mu, Sigma)\n",
    "\n",
    "mu_hat = simulated_returns.mean(axis=0)\n",
    "Sigma_hat = np.cov(simulated_returns, rowvar=False, ddof=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "frontier_hat = compute_efficient_frontier(mu_hat, Sigma_hat, n_points=100)\n",
    "tangency_hat = compute_tangency_portfolio(mu_hat, Sigma_hat)"
